  "cooking_instructions": [
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Preheat the oven to 200&deg;C/ 180&deg;C (fan)/ 400&deg;F/ Gas 6</p>\r\n<p>Peel and finely slice the<strong> red onion<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong></p>\r\n<p>Deseed the<strong> red pepper<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> (scrape the seeds and pith out with a teaspoon) and cut into thin strips</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 1,
      "image": "/images/instructions/beef-and-chorizo-chilli-with-lime/step-1.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Heat a large, wide-based pan (preferably non-stick) with a matching lid, with a drizzle of <strong>vegetable oil</strong> over a medium-low heat</p>\r\n<p>Once hot, add the <strong>sliced&nbsp;</strong><strong>pepper</strong> and <strong>sliced&nbsp;onion</strong> with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>,<strong>&nbsp;pepper</strong>&nbsp;and&nbsp;<strong>sugar&nbsp;</strong>and cook for 10 min, or until everything has softened</p>",
      "order": 2,
      "image": "/images/instructions/beef-and-chorizo-chilli-with-lime/step-2.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, add the <strong>basmati rice</strong> and 175ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[350ml]</span> <strong>cold water</strong> to a pot with a lid and bring to the boil over a high heat</p>\r\n<p>Once boiling, reduce the heat to very low and cook, covered, for 10-15 min or until all the water has absorbed and the rice is cooked</p>\r\n<p>Once cooked, remove from the heat and keep covered until serving</p>\r\n<p>&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 3,
      "image": "/images/instructions/beef-and-chorizo-chilli-with-lime/step-3.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Meanwhile, cut each&nbsp;<strong>tortilla</strong>&nbsp;into three so you are left with large<strong> tortilla shards&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Tip: stack them up before cutting to speed up the process!</p>\r\n<p>Add the <strong>tortilla shards</strong> to a baking tray (or two!), drizzle with <strong>olive oil</strong>, season with a pinch of<strong> salt</strong>&nbsp;and put the tray in the oven for 10 min or until they're crispy</p>\r\n<p>Tip: you may need to do this in batches!&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 4,
      "image": "/images/instructions/beef-and-chorizo-chilli-with-lime/step-4.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Boil a kettle&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Cut the <strong>mini chorizo sausages</strong> in half&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Dissolve the <strong>tomato paste</strong> in 350ml <span class=\"text-danger\">[700ml]</span> <strong>boiled water&nbsp;</strong>- this is your <strong>tomato stock</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cut the <strong>lime<span class=\"text-danger\">[s]</span></strong> into wedges&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 5,
      "image": "/images/instructions/beef-and-chorizo-chilli-with-lime/step-5.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Once the<strong> pepper</strong>&nbsp;and<strong>&nbsp;onion</strong>&nbsp;have softened, transfer them to a plate and set aside</p>\r\n<p>Return the pan to a high heat and once hot, add the <strong>chorizo</strong> and <strong>beef mince&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Cook for 4 min or until browned, breaking the mince up with a wooden spoon as you go</p>\r\n<p>Once browned, return the <strong>pepper</strong>&nbsp;and <strong>onion</strong> to the pan with the<strong>&nbsp;smoked paprika</strong> and<strong> chipotle paste</strong> and cook for 1 min</p>",
      "order": 6,
      "image": "/images/instructions/beef-and-chorizo-chilli-with-lime/step-6.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Add the <strong>tomato stock</strong> to the pan with a generous pinch of <strong>salt</strong>&nbsp; and<strong> pepper</strong> and cook, covered, for 4-5 min or until thickened to a chilli-like consistency&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Meanwhile, chop the <strong>coriander</strong> finely, including the stalks&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Grate the<strong> cheddar cheese&nbsp;</strong></p>\r\n<p>Squeeze the juice of half the<strong> lime wedges</strong> into the<strong> cooked</strong>&nbsp;<strong>basmati rice</strong> and season with a pinch of&nbsp;<strong>salt</strong>&nbsp;- this is your <strong>lime rice</strong></p>",
      "order": 7,
      "image": "/images/instructions/beef-and-chorizo-chilli-with-lime/step-7.jpg"
    },
    {
      "instruction": "<p>Serve the <strong>beef and chorizo&nbsp;chilli</strong> over the<strong> lime</strong>&nbsp;<strong>rice</strong></p>\r\n<p>Top with the <strong>grated cheese</strong> and <strong>chopped coriander</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Garnish with a wedge of <strong>lime</strong>&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Serve the <strong>crispy tortilla shards</strong> in the middle of the table for sharing&nbsp;</p>\r\n<p>Enjoy!&nbsp;</p>",
      "order": 8
    }
  ],
